properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Manasquan Inlet to Little Egg Inlet NJ out 20 nm; Coastal waters from Sandy Hook to Manasquan Inlet NJ out 20 nm
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 14 at 6:16PM EST until January 17 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
seas 3 to 6 feet possible.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Sandy Hook to Manasquan Inlet NJ
out 20 nm and Coastal waters from Manasquan Inlet to Little
Egg Inlet NJ out 20 nm.

* WHEN...From Thursday morning through Friday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY MORNING THROUGH FRIDAY MORNING
